1
00:00:05,495 --> 00:00:07,165
(conflict sound)

2
00:00:07,165 --> 00:00:10,132
(Yume) I pressed it (Mio) Huh?

3
00:00:10,132 --> 00:00:14,528
Pushing Mio's mother's back...

4
00:00:14,528 --> 00:00:17,066
I was the one who pushed it down.

5
00:00:19,198 --> 00:00:21,264
(impact sound)

6
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:25,825
Mio-chan... Ah!

7
00:00:30,726 --> 00:00:34,099
(breathing heavily)

8
00:00:34,099 --> 00:00:36,264
Mio-chan... Hey, don't come!

9
00:00:36,264 --> 00:00:41,132
(breathing heavily)

10
00:00:41,132 --> 00:00:45,627
I'm really... sorry...

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,924
(buzzer sound)

12
00:00:50,924 --> 00:00:53,825
Hey Mio-chan... let me out! Open it quickly!

13
00:00:53,825 --> 00:00:55,495
If you press it too many times it will break

14
00:00:55,495 --> 00:01:00,462
It's broken so it's stopped! (buzzer sound)

15
00:01:00,462 --> 00:01:04,924
I'm really... I'm really sorry, wait a minute.

16
00:01:04,924 --> 00:01:06,957
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait...

17
00:01:06,957 --> 00:01:09,066
scary scary scary scary scary scary

18
00:01:09,066 --> 00:01:13,132
What? From where? Which part is a lie?

19
00:01:13,132 --> 00:01:19,594
What about anonymous reports? Pretending you were a man?

20
00:01:21,561 --> 00:01:25,198
Because I was with Sakuma-san... At that time

21
00:01:27,132 --> 00:01:30,165
There was a day when we went to the rooftop together, right?

22
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:35,165
That day...

23
00:01:35,165 --> 00:01:38,396
Sakuma-san also went to the rooftop.

24
00:01:40,132 --> 00:01:42,264
Huh?

25
00:01:42,264 --> 00:01:45,759
There's probably a beer receipt on the roof.

26
00:01:45,759 --> 00:01:51,825
I thought maybe I had left it behind...and...

27
00:01:51,825 --> 00:01:58,363
So you were with me to destroy evidence?

28
00:01:58,363 --> 00:02:01,462
So... what about moving?

29
00:02:01,462 --> 00:02:04,363
Was that also a deliberate arrangement? You mean you approached me?

30
00:02:04,363 --> 00:02:09,000
That's true, even if it's just a coincidence...

31
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,759
I've always been curious about the fact that he came home with a suicide note...

32
00:02:12,759 --> 00:02:15,594
I met Mio-chan who was really depressed...

33
00:02:15,594 --> 00:02:18,000
“We met”?

34
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,495
That's not what I meant... Well, if we never met...

35
00:02:21,495 --> 00:02:23,396
Stay silent for the rest of your life

36
00:02:23,396 --> 00:02:26,561
So you were planning to run away and leave the will behind?

37
00:02:33,363 --> 00:02:35,594
(buzzer sound)

38
00:02:35,594 --> 00:02:38,396
Hey Mio-chan... don't touch me!

39
00:02:42,462 --> 00:02:45,858
With that hand...

40
00:02:45,858 --> 00:02:50,759
You mean you killed your mother?

41
00:02:56,924 --> 00:03:01,561
Who is it? You

42
00:03:09,099 --> 00:03:12,561
Excuse me. Are you okay?

43
00:03:15,726 --> 00:03:19,000
Oh, hey... Hey, hey!

44
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:35,165
♬〜

45
00:03:39,495 --> 00:03:44,495
Why didn't you come forward right away?

46
00:03:47,495 --> 00:03:51,891
(Endo) Why did you run away from the scene?

47
00:03:56,132 --> 00:03:59,759
Because I thought I couldn't take it back

48
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:02,858
(Sakuma) I thought he might have left a receipt behind.

49
00:04:02,858 --> 00:04:05,561
Hear from her...

50
00:04:05,561 --> 00:04:11,363
So I thought I should collect the receipt...

51
00:04:11,363 --> 00:04:14,198
I entered that building.

52
00:04:14,198 --> 00:04:16,561
How is that?

53
00:04:18,429 --> 00:04:20,099
Huh?

54
00:04:20,099 --> 00:04:23,594
(Endo) Even though you have so many secrets,

55
00:04:23,594 --> 00:04:28,396
Why do I have a friend-like relationship with Mio Osako?

56
00:04:28,396 --> 00:04:30,561
Did you continue?

57
00:04:34,264 --> 00:04:36,363
I don't understand

58
00:04:40,462 --> 00:04:42,561
I'm ready

59
00:04:42,561 --> 00:04:50,495
♬〜

60
00:04:50,495 --> 00:04:54,528
You really didn't know anything?

61
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:57,495
Huh? You live together, right?

62
00:04:57,495 --> 00:05:00,462
You'll notice something, right?

63
00:05:00,462 --> 00:05:02,660
Isn't that the case too?

64
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:06,231
I'm so sticky, even though I drink and hang out and talk to girls every day.

65
00:05:06,231 --> 00:05:08,825
You didn't notice anything?

66
00:05:08,825 --> 00:05:19,231
♬〜

67
00:05:19,231 --> 00:05:21,858
Sister, I think she's going to jail.

68
00:05:21,858 --> 00:05:24,825
You're going, right? Well, you're killing someone.

69
00:05:29,132 --> 00:05:34,165
I'm back to square one

70
00:05:34,165 --> 00:05:40,627
♬〜

71
00:05:40,627 --> 00:05:45,594
It's just us. Without knowing it, we were fooled.

72
00:05:45,594 --> 00:05:47,264
Huh?

73
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:50,231
Kondo-san knew

74
00:05:52,165 --> 00:05:53,825
Huh?

75
00:05:53,825 --> 00:06:13,000
♬〜

76
00:06:14,726 --> 00:06:19,693
(Sae) Hey, what does this mean? You had it, right?

77
00:06:19,693 --> 00:06:22,066
what? I don't know this at all...

78
00:06:22,066 --> 00:06:23,726
Answer!

79
00:06:32,462 --> 00:06:34,627
(sound of door opening)

80
00:06:44,594 --> 00:06:46,264
(Endo) From over there

81
00:06:55,627 --> 00:06:58,660
Huh? Hey, hey!

82
00:07:03,396 --> 00:07:05,396
What do you mean you can't arrest me?

83
00:07:05,396 --> 00:07:08,198
(Endo) It hasn't been decided yet.

84
00:07:08,198 --> 00:07:10,627
At present, no arrests will be made immediately.

85
00:07:10,627 --> 00:07:12,759
What? Even though I pushed her back and pushed her down?

86
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:15,693
(Endo) Of course, if there was murderous intent, you can be charged with a crime.

87
00:07:15,693 --> 00:07:19,660
However, in her case, she was surprised by a pigeon that suddenly flew out.

88
00:07:19,660 --> 00:07:21,759
In other words, this falls under the category of force majeure.

89
00:07:21,759 --> 00:07:23,528
It's possible that there was no murderous intent.

90
00:07:23,528 --> 00:07:25,891
How do you know? Mr. Osako...

91
00:07:25,891 --> 00:07:29,000
Isn't this the woman who has been lying to me and pretending to be my friend?

92
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,792
What that person says is true

93
00:07:30,792 --> 00:07:32,462
How do you know there was no murderous intent?

94
00:07:32,462 --> 00:07:37,099
Proof that there was no murderous intent, and proof that there was murderous intent.

95
00:07:37,099 --> 00:07:40,297
It's extremely difficult now that there are no other witnesses.

96
00:07:40,297 --> 00:07:44,462
Huh? So what are the police for?

97
00:07:46,099 --> 00:07:53,330
The fact is that your mother went up to the roof with this suicide note.

98
00:07:53,330 --> 00:07:56,528
This will is definitely your mother's handwriting.

99
00:07:56,528 --> 00:07:58,429
And Yume Nakata wrote this will.

100
00:07:58,429 --> 00:08:01,858
He stated that he brought it back from the rooftop.

101
00:08:01,858 --> 00:08:04,264
Mother tried to commit suicide

102
00:08:04,264 --> 00:08:06,660
The very fact that he climbed onto the roof himself

103
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:09,858
I understand how you feel, but I'm not trying to hide it...

104
00:08:09,858 --> 00:08:12,066
If so, please throw me in jail.

105
00:08:12,066 --> 00:08:16,330
(Endo) Mr. Osako, I am not convinced at all.

106
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:20,396
Until I find out everything she did once again.

107
00:08:20,396 --> 00:08:22,693
I absolutely...

108
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:27,165
(Sound of door opening and closing)

109
00:08:27,165 --> 00:08:47,165
♬〜

110
00:08:47,165 --> 00:08:48,825
♬〜

111
00:08:48,825 --> 00:08:53,132
Taro... (Sound of door opening and closing)

112
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:54,792
Taro

113
00:08:56,792 --> 00:08:58,462
sorry…

114
00:09:11,825 --> 00:09:14,594
(coughing)

115
00:09:14,594 --> 00:09:21,561
♬〜

116
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,462
(coughing)

117
00:09:24,462 --> 00:09:44,462
♬〜

118
00:09:44,462 --> 00:09:46,528
♬〜

119
00:09:46,528 --> 00:09:48,198
(sound of breathing)

120
00:09:48,198 --> 00:10:08,198
♬〜

121
00:10:08,198 --> 00:10:10,099
♬〜

122
00:10:11,099 --> 00:10:20,495
(chime)

123
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:27,693
(Yonemoto) Good morning, this is Kairiki Moving Center.

124
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:29,363
Thank you very much for your help today...

125
00:10:29,363 --> 00:10:31,231
Excuse me, can I cancel please?

126
00:10:31,231 --> 00:10:32,891
(Yonemoto) Huh? I'm really sorry

127
00:10:32,891 --> 00:10:36,198
No, wait...um...it's canceled on the same day.

128
00:10:36,198 --> 00:10:39,429
You will be charged 100% of the fee...

129
00:10:39,429 --> 00:10:41,759
Huh? (Yonemoto) Simple stretch plan

130
00:10:41,759 --> 00:10:43,726
13,600 yen

131
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:47,825
Sorry! Um... cancel!

132
00:10:47,825 --> 00:10:50,462
(Yonemoto) Nakata! Why are you late? I can't answer the phone!

133
00:10:50,462 --> 00:10:52,132
Sorry, that...

134
00:10:52,132 --> 00:10:54,264
Well, I'll get the money, so please wait a moment.

135
00:10:54,264 --> 00:10:58,033
No, I'll pay the money.

136
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:01,231
(Yonemoto) Huh? Sorry, then.

137
00:11:01,231 --> 00:11:04,066
This... Mio-chan!

138
00:11:05,528 --> 00:11:09,330
Mio-chan... Really...

139
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:11,825
shoes

140
00:11:11,825 --> 00:11:13,957
sorry…

141
00:11:13,957 --> 00:11:16,264
I'm really sorry...

142
00:11:20,165 --> 00:11:24,759
Um...tell Kondo-san the truth too.

143
00:11:24,759 --> 00:11:27,495
I was thinking about doing things properly, such as disinheritance.

144
00:11:27,495 --> 00:11:30,792
Endo-san stopped me...

145
00:11:34,165 --> 00:11:36,429
Actually, I was told not to come here either.

146
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:41,033
But Mio-chan, there's no need to let go of this house...

147
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:44,330
Is that story over already?

148
00:11:44,330 --> 00:11:48,396
Mr. Kondo knows everything too.

149
00:11:48,396 --> 00:11:52,033
That's good...

150
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:55,033
"good"?

151
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:57,429
That's not what I mean...

152
00:11:59,264 --> 00:12:05,330
Endo-san, I want to hear the story properly once again.

153
00:12:05,330 --> 00:12:07,726
when?

154
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,858
tomorrow

155
00:12:09,858 --> 00:12:15,231
So everything I did there...

156
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:21,957
Mio-chan...

157
00:12:23,858 --> 00:12:26,792
If you don't come home, I'll call the police.

158
00:12:52,891 --> 00:12:54,561
(Sakura) Hey

159
00:12:54,561 --> 00:13:03,297
♬〜

160
00:13:03,297 --> 00:13:08,000
(Sakura) Did you go to school? I took a day off today

161
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,561
Hey, aren't you going home? (Taro) Do you need something?

162
00:13:16,957 --> 00:13:20,726
I wanted to apologize properly

163
00:13:20,726 --> 00:13:23,693
Sorry for being silent

164
00:13:27,924 --> 00:13:32,099
No... But it's for you, right?

165
00:13:32,099 --> 00:13:36,330
If your sister gets arrested for telling the truth...

166
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:40,033
Then I had to go back to my mom again.

167
00:13:40,033 --> 00:13:43,957
Uzee (Sakura) Huh?

168
00:13:47,297 --> 00:13:50,165
I'm not talking about Mr. Kondo.

169
00:13:50,165 --> 00:13:53,033
I didn't just like your face

170
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:57,660
No, well, it's 80% of the face.

171
00:13:57,660 --> 00:14:00,264
But the remaining 20%...

172
00:14:02,429 --> 00:14:06,891
Because the things I hate are the same

173
00:14:11,264 --> 00:14:15,033
Because I'm a person who gets really angry about things like that.

174
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:16,693
I liked it

175
00:14:20,033 --> 00:14:25,594
(Taro) But in the end, I'm the biggest liar.

176
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,693
In that case, it's much better to be ignored.

177
00:14:33,693 --> 00:14:35,363
(Sakura) Huh?

178
00:14:39,132 --> 00:14:40,792
(Sakura) Taro!

179
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,792
After all, Yokya was an idiot.

180
00:14:48,792 --> 00:15:01,792
♬〜

181
00:15:01,792 --> 00:15:04,726
(Sound of door opening) Yes, yes.

182
00:15:14,363 --> 00:15:22,231
From here... Find Misato-san standing on the edge.

183
00:15:22,231 --> 00:15:25,924
I have a beer. “Do you want to drink it?”

184
00:15:30,627 --> 00:15:33,528
(Klaxon)

185
00:15:33,528 --> 00:15:36,000
(Male) Oh! Don't be silly!

186
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:48,693
I tried to head towards Sakuma-san who was downstairs...

187
00:15:51,528 --> 00:15:53,198
Mio-chan...

188
00:15:56,033 --> 00:15:59,792
(Endo) Osako-san, why? What happened?

189
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,462
(Endo) Yume Nakata

190
00:16:01,462 --> 00:16:03,858
I feel like I'm being told the truth

191
00:16:03,858 --> 00:16:06,363
The results of re-verification based on her testimony

192
00:16:06,363 --> 00:16:09,495
There are no discrepancies with what we investigated immediately after the accident.

193
00:16:09,495 --> 00:16:11,165
It has been determined that it was an unexpected accident.Okay, okay.

194
00:16:11,165 --> 00:16:14,495
Okay, okay, give me a hundred steps, pigeon, okay?

195
00:16:14,495 --> 00:16:16,693
Let's just say it's the pigeon's fault.

196
00:16:16,693 --> 00:16:18,825
But what about after that?

197
00:16:20,627 --> 00:16:22,429
You ran away, right?

198
00:16:22,429 --> 00:16:26,099
I left Mr. Kondo with my mother who was a mess from the blood flow.

199
00:16:26,099 --> 00:16:31,462
I understand how you feel...but you don't understand! not at all!

200
00:16:31,462 --> 00:16:33,726
It's different

201
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:36,825
Because if I had known all of this from the beginning

202
00:16:36,825 --> 00:16:41,462
Up until now, I was completely different.

203
00:16:41,462 --> 00:16:45,330
I was told that I was the daughter of a selfish woman who got involved and died on her own.

204
00:16:45,330 --> 00:16:47,495
Being looked down upon by the world

205
00:16:47,495 --> 00:16:51,264
I was kicked out of the house and carried the burden of my parents' sins.

206
00:16:51,264 --> 00:16:54,066
``I'd rather be unhappy than I am for the rest of my life.''

207
00:16:54,066 --> 00:16:57,033
That's what Mr. Kondo's daughter told me.

208
00:17:00,429 --> 00:17:04,000
That person will not be charged with a crime.

209
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,792
Things that I have been suffering from for a long time

210
00:17:06,792 --> 00:17:10,561
I keep thinking about why my mom died.

211
00:17:10,561 --> 00:17:14,429
Does that mean all of that doesn't matter?

212
00:17:14,429 --> 00:17:20,165
As I mentioned before, my mother...

213
00:17:20,165 --> 00:17:24,363
There is no denying the fact that he climbed onto the roof of his own free will.

214
00:17:24,363 --> 00:17:26,726
So you don't know that either, right? I'm a person who lies without hesitation.

215
00:17:26,726 --> 00:17:30,165
Mr. Osako, no. Isn't it strange?

216
00:17:30,165 --> 00:17:31,825
Well then what?

217
00:17:31,825 --> 00:17:34,528
What if what that woman said was true?

218
00:17:34,528 --> 00:17:36,957
what? Just when I thought I was going to die, beer came?

219
00:17:36,957 --> 00:17:39,495
in? He said he flipped the sauce on the ramen.

220
00:17:39,495 --> 00:17:44,396
Just hearing such a stupid story made me say, ``I'm going to live''...

221
00:17:58,891 --> 00:18:01,495
Enough is enough

222
00:18:01,495 --> 00:18:03,231
hang on!

223
00:18:10,396 --> 00:18:12,792
Why did you run away?

224
00:18:20,660 --> 00:18:22,660
sorry…

225
00:18:23,792 --> 00:18:27,924
Why did you pretend to be my friend?

226
00:18:27,924 --> 00:18:30,165
It's not pretend

227
00:18:32,693 --> 00:18:34,528
Mio-chan!

228
00:18:42,198 --> 00:18:44,825
I don't want to see you again for the rest of my life

229
00:18:47,792 --> 00:18:52,957
If you appear in front of me next...

230
00:18:52,957 --> 00:18:55,660
Maybe I'll kill you.

231
00:18:58,132 --> 00:19:00,396
Mio-chan... don't move!

232
00:19:08,627 --> 00:19:12,660
(Endo) Osako-san, wait a minute... Osako-san!

233
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:14,759
I know I'm saying something harsh, but...

234
00:19:14,759 --> 00:19:16,462
The only thing you'll do wrong is...

235
00:19:16,462 --> 00:19:18,891
Does that mean you'll arrest me if I do it?

236
00:19:18,891 --> 00:19:20,561
Eh...

237
00:19:26,561 --> 00:19:32,231
I'm really sorry

238
00:19:32,231 --> 00:19:47,825
♬〜

239
00:19:47,825 --> 00:19:54,165
When we're talking about compensation for damages here.

240
00:19:54,165 --> 00:19:57,957
You came with Mr. Osako, right?

241
00:19:57,957 --> 00:20:00,495
yes

242
00:20:00,495 --> 00:20:04,198
Approach my daughter...

243
00:20:04,198 --> 00:20:08,792
I told you to keep quiet about the letter because I would pay you 1 million yen.

244
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:11,099
Is that the time?

245
00:20:13,891 --> 00:20:20,198
How did you feel about coming here with Mr. Osako?

246
00:20:20,198 --> 00:20:28,627
♬〜

247
00:20:28,627 --> 00:20:32,495
I'm really sorry

248
00:20:32,495 --> 00:20:34,165
(Hiroshi) Get out.

249
00:20:34,165 --> 00:20:54,165
♬〜

250
00:20:54,165 --> 00:21:14,165
♬〜

251
00:21:14,165 --> 00:21:34,165
♬〜

252
00:21:34,165 --> 00:21:35,825
♬〜

253
00:21:35,825 --> 00:21:37,891
Excuse me

254
00:21:37,891 --> 00:21:44,825
♬〜

255
00:21:47,165 --> 00:21:49,297
Why are you here?

256
00:21:49,297 --> 00:21:51,627
what? that bangs

257
00:21:52,759 --> 00:21:55,924
What about Taro? Why aren't you answering the phone?

258
00:21:55,924 --> 00:21:59,429
(sound of door opening)

259
00:21:59,429 --> 00:22:01,099
Taro...

260
00:22:01,099 --> 00:22:03,726
(Chihiro) I want to come back here.

261
00:22:03,726 --> 00:22:05,396
Huh? (Chihiro) Just leave without permission.

262
00:22:05,396 --> 00:22:07,264
You have a good status.

263
00:22:07,264 --> 00:22:11,627
Well, I don't understand how you feel, but this time

264
00:22:11,627 --> 00:22:16,891
in? What's the situation now? Huh?

265
00:22:16,891 --> 00:22:20,396
As long as it's not a crime and you won't be arrested.

266
00:22:20,396 --> 00:22:22,957
I asked Taro everything.

267
00:22:28,726 --> 00:22:33,033
(Chihiro) What? It can't be helped to see Taro like that, right?

268
00:22:33,033 --> 00:22:37,759
I'm actually glad you told me.

269
00:22:37,759 --> 00:22:39,858
It has nothing to do with mom

270
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:42,759
I'm sure it's related!

271
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:44,462
Something like this leaked out

272
00:22:44,462 --> 00:22:47,429
What would happen if the media or SNS made a fuss about it?

273
00:22:47,429 --> 00:22:49,594
Something about a cram school run by a murderous mother.

274
00:22:49,594 --> 00:22:54,759
Who wants to send their child to school? What about Saya-chan and dad?

275
00:22:54,759 --> 00:22:56,429
(sigh)

276
00:22:56,429 --> 00:23:03,495
Are you saying you'd be in trouble if your current life was messed up?

277
00:23:03,495 --> 00:23:07,825
I'll definitely be in trouble if a lawsuit is brought against me.

278
00:23:07,825 --> 00:23:10,726
For now, please consult with your mother's lawyer.

279
00:23:10,726 --> 00:23:13,066
Mr. Kondo who was involved

280
00:23:13,066 --> 00:23:17,099
Also, the daughter of the person you killed? Mr. Osako?

281
00:23:17,099 --> 00:23:18,924
Pay a settlement fee to two people

282
00:23:18,924 --> 00:23:21,132
I have to take a proactive approach to keep it all in a circle.

283
00:23:21,132 --> 00:23:22,825
It's not a matter of money, right?

284
00:23:22,825 --> 00:23:26,132
There are only two ways to deal with a mistake

285
00:23:26,132 --> 00:23:29,330
Can you solve it with money or just ignore it?

286
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:31,759
You couldn't escape this time.

287
00:23:31,759 --> 00:23:35,891
It's my fault that only money can solve the problem...

288
00:23:35,891 --> 00:23:37,561
Are people dying?

289
00:23:37,561 --> 00:23:41,462
I know! That kind of thing

290
00:23:41,462 --> 00:23:44,924
People die because you do unnecessary things.

291
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:47,627
This is the second time with Dad, right?

292
00:23:52,495 --> 00:23:56,693
Mom will do something anyway.

293
00:23:56,693 --> 00:24:00,033
It's not for you, it's to protect my life.

294
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:05,264
So don't do anything unnecessary anymore.

295
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:10,495
Because it's my problem

296
00:24:10,495 --> 00:24:14,561
I'll do it myself... (Taro) It's impossible for my sister.

297
00:24:16,759 --> 00:24:18,429
Huh?

298
00:24:18,429 --> 00:24:24,000
If my sister tries hard, everything will go wrong.

299
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,561
I've always thought about my father

300
00:24:27,561 --> 00:24:32,396
I thought my sister wasn't wrong.

301
00:24:32,396 --> 00:24:35,099
but…

302
00:24:35,099 --> 00:24:38,858
Because of who my sister is?

303
00:24:38,858 --> 00:24:41,726
Want to help...

304
00:24:43,825 --> 00:24:45,627
Every time I do something like that, I do it like this

305
00:24:45,627 --> 00:24:48,495
Everyone around me is unhappy.

306
00:24:53,693 --> 00:24:56,099
So after all...

307
00:24:58,627 --> 00:25:02,231
I think my sister is wrong.

308
00:25:17,495 --> 00:25:19,165
《Ugh...》

309
00:25:23,858 --> 00:25:28,660
(Chihiro)《I wish it had all been a dream...》

310
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:31,891
《That you were born》

311
00:25:35,495 --> 00:25:38,891
♬(Music playing from the speaker)

312
00:25:38,891 --> 00:25:45,561
♬(Everyone) You are my friend, the friend I can talk to all the time.

313
00:25:45,561 --> 00:25:49,033
♬Even if I'm rubbed by the rough tide

314
00:25:49,033 --> 00:25:52,429
♬I'm fine. Why is that?

315
00:25:52,429 --> 00:25:55,726
♬Because I have you, I am my friend

316
00:25:55,726 --> 00:25:58,891
♬Overcome the difficulties, let's go

317
00:25:58,891 --> 00:26:02,297
♬I am a squid and you are a shellfish

318
00:26:02,297 --> 00:26:05,726
♬If you read it upside down, squid is chi

319
00:26:05,726 --> 00:26:08,627
♬ Good friends, are you good today too? delicious squid

320
00:26:08,627 --> 00:26:12,792
♬ Let's eat it with all our friends (Bada) That's it!

321
00:26:12,792 --> 00:26:16,429
♬(All) Delicious Squid Fisheries (Mada) Yes!

322
00:26:16,429 --> 00:26:20,825
(applause)

323
00:26:21,924 --> 00:26:24,495
(Shiono) It's a strange company song, isn't it?

324
00:26:24,495 --> 00:26:27,396
“If you read it upside down, it’s squid”… haha

325
00:26:27,396 --> 00:26:30,231
Does it seriously make no sense?

326
00:26:32,594 --> 00:26:36,825
Mr. Osako? Huh? Ah, right.

327
00:26:38,726 --> 00:26:40,528
Is that enough? paid

328
00:26:40,528 --> 00:26:44,924
Huh? Ah... Yeah, was it okay?

329
00:26:44,924 --> 00:26:47,099
No, that's totally fine.

330
00:26:47,099 --> 00:26:50,396
No, I heard that they stopped moving.

331
00:26:50,396 --> 00:26:52,693
Did something happen?

332
00:26:59,132 --> 00:27:02,264
Shiono-kun... Huh?

333
00:27:02,264 --> 00:27:05,726
What do you do when your guts boil over?

334
00:27:05,726 --> 00:27:08,363
(Shiono) Huh?

335
00:27:08,363 --> 00:27:11,231
In anger

336
00:27:11,231 --> 00:27:14,495
When my stomach is boiling

337
00:27:14,495 --> 00:27:18,792
Ah... no, but what about cooking?

338
00:27:18,792 --> 00:27:20,495
cooking?

339
00:27:20,495 --> 00:27:22,561
Is chicken good?

340
00:27:22,561 --> 00:27:27,198
If there's someone you're angry with...

341
00:27:27,198 --> 00:27:32,132
Think of that face...

342
00:27:34,858 --> 00:27:36,528
(Shiono)Cut

343
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,132
I cut a lot

344
00:27:41,495 --> 00:27:44,198
(Mada) You have a wife, right?

345
00:27:44,198 --> 00:27:46,495
Child How old are you? (Employee) High school student

346
00:27:46,495 --> 00:27:48,297
(Mada) High school student? high school student?

347
00:27:48,297 --> 00:27:52,099
Oh, I'm not doing anything weird.

348
00:27:52,099 --> 00:27:57,264
Does cooking unify your mind? It means being able to be selfless.

349
00:27:58,330 --> 00:28:02,495
Ah... That's right, cooking (Shiono) Yes.

350
00:28:44,495 --> 00:28:49,792
(Sae) Um... I'm sorry for everything.

351
00:28:49,792 --> 00:28:53,495
Um... please

352
00:29:05,198 --> 00:29:08,561
Husband, how are you doing now?

353
00:29:08,561 --> 00:29:12,924
Yeah, I've been feeling good lately. I've started rehabilitation.

354
00:29:12,924 --> 00:29:15,759
It looks like I'll be able to walk somehow

355
00:29:15,759 --> 00:29:19,396
I see, that was really good

356
00:29:19,396 --> 00:29:22,660
But that doesn't mean it's completely back to normal.

357
00:29:22,660 --> 00:29:27,561
I don't think it will happen to me or Sakura's life either.

358
00:29:35,891 --> 00:29:38,429
(Sae) This

359
00:29:38,429 --> 00:29:42,000
Huh? this…

360
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:46,561
The girl had the letter that person wrote to you.

361
00:29:46,561 --> 00:29:51,858
Huh... when and where...

362
00:29:51,858 --> 00:29:53,891
(Sae) I ate gyoza here.

363
00:29:53,891 --> 00:29:58,330
At that time, my daughter said that she made various threats to you...

364
00:29:58,330 --> 00:30:00,363
I'm sorry, no...

365
00:30:00,363 --> 00:30:04,231
Um... Yume wrote this...

366
00:30:04,231 --> 00:30:08,528
(Sae) I'll pay you 1 million yen, so please shut up.

367
00:30:08,528 --> 00:30:11,330
Huh? (Sae) My daughter found it.

368
00:30:11,330 --> 00:30:14,495
He paid his daughter 1 million yen to keep quiet about this.

369
00:30:14,495 --> 00:30:16,528
It seems like you said that

370
00:30:18,363 --> 00:30:21,033
(Sae) That money is still in my house.

371
00:30:21,033 --> 00:30:23,429
I feel bad about giving it back.

372
00:30:23,429 --> 00:30:26,429
I'm planning to use the money to pay for my husband's treatment.

373
00:30:26,429 --> 00:30:28,099
Huh?

374
00:30:28,099 --> 00:30:31,594
So I've already paid for the treatment.

375
00:30:31,594 --> 00:30:35,825
Please give me back what I have received so far.

376
00:30:52,495 --> 00:30:56,825
(Sae) Um... do you have any alcohol? Huh?

377
00:30:56,825 --> 00:31:02,132
I don't really like shochu, but other than that,

378
00:31:02,132 --> 00:31:04,297
ah…

379
00:31:14,429 --> 00:31:16,099
that…

380
00:31:29,396 --> 00:31:35,198
It was my fault that my husband was walking over there that day.

381
00:31:35,198 --> 00:31:36,858
Huh?

382
00:31:37,858 --> 00:31:42,264
That day was the first time I said, "I want a divorce."

383
00:31:42,264 --> 00:31:45,924
I was finally able to say that I felt refreshed.

384
00:31:45,924 --> 00:31:48,660
But then my husband got angry

385
00:31:48,660 --> 00:31:51,363
I said, ``I'm getting a cold head,'' and left.

386
00:31:51,363 --> 00:31:54,198
I was thinking that I should cool my head down

387
00:31:54,198 --> 00:31:57,660
I received a call from the emergency personnel...

388
00:32:00,330 --> 00:32:03,462
I thought it was my fault

389
00:32:03,462 --> 00:32:08,858
If I hadn't talked about divorce, my husband wouldn't have been walking there.

390
00:32:10,231 --> 00:32:17,099
(Sae) So... I pretended to love my husband.

391
00:32:17,099 --> 00:32:19,495
I'm not talking about divorce.

392
00:32:19,495 --> 00:32:23,627
My husband just got caught up in it.

393
00:32:26,858 --> 00:32:30,561
(Sae) But married couples are weird, aren't they?

394
00:32:30,561 --> 00:32:33,957
No... maybe I'm weird...

395
00:32:36,363 --> 00:32:43,033
I was pretending like that when Sakura was born.

396
00:32:43,033 --> 00:32:45,594
My first time with that person was at a red lantern pub.

397
00:32:45,594 --> 00:32:49,396
I remembered the time I ate giblets stew.

398
00:32:50,924 --> 00:32:55,858
Did I start to love again? Was it just a pretend after all?

399
00:32:55,858 --> 00:32:58,858
I still don't understand

400
00:33:04,198 --> 00:33:08,462
Being a mother is boring, isn't it?

401
00:33:10,363 --> 00:33:12,033
Huh?

402
00:33:12,033 --> 00:33:20,495
My daughter... knew about the divorce.

403
00:33:20,495 --> 00:33:25,495
You probably don't like it when your mother shakes like this...

404
00:33:25,495 --> 00:33:28,297
It was awkward...

405
00:33:28,297 --> 00:33:40,330
♬〜

406
00:33:40,330 --> 00:33:44,891
Would you like to file a lawsuit together?

407
00:33:44,891 --> 00:33:46,561
Huh?

408
00:33:46,561 --> 00:33:49,066
Of course it's also about money.

409
00:33:49,066 --> 00:33:53,330
I'll file a lawsuit and let the world know.

410
00:33:53,330 --> 00:33:56,033
You said that, right?

411
00:33:56,033 --> 00:33:58,660
``If there's someone who pushed your mother down,

412
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:01,462
That person is the one to blame."

413
00:34:01,462 --> 00:34:03,726
Does that mean he's the worst?

414
00:34:03,726 --> 00:34:08,099
If that's the case, I won't be able to calm down unless I hurt you thoroughly.

415
00:34:08,099 --> 00:34:14,462
♬〜

416
00:34:14,462 --> 00:34:18,957
(Sae) Did you run away? That person

417
00:34:18,957 --> 00:34:22,396
leave your mother and husband behind

418
00:34:24,264 --> 00:34:29,165
Can you forgive me like this? About that person

419
00:34:29,165 --> 00:34:38,000
♬〜

420
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:57,429
(chime)

421
00:35:06,495 --> 00:35:09,462
Ah... Ah! Go...

422
00:35:09,462 --> 00:35:12,561
It hurts...

423
00:35:12,561 --> 00:35:17,165
Sorry, that...

424
00:35:18,891 --> 00:35:21,627
I want to apologize properly...

425
00:35:28,957 --> 00:35:32,858
Really…

426
00:35:32,858 --> 00:35:36,000
I'm sorry

427
00:35:39,660 --> 00:35:41,858
About Yume...

428
00:35:44,957 --> 00:35:53,099
There has been no contact, right?

429
00:35:53,099 --> 00:36:00,627
I haven't been able to contact you for a long time, and my company has been closed for a long time.

430
00:36:00,627 --> 00:36:05,066
The phone... even when I went home, it wasn't answered.

431
00:36:06,066 --> 00:36:11,264
If I just leave it alone like this...

432
00:36:11,264 --> 00:36:13,891
I thought I might die...

433
00:36:15,264 --> 00:36:18,363
That's the worst I...

434
00:36:20,726 --> 00:36:24,693
Excuse me... for bothering you.

435
00:36:26,264 --> 00:36:29,429
What's the worst?

436
00:36:29,429 --> 00:36:31,825
Huh?

437
00:36:31,825 --> 00:36:37,396
How did you feel when you came here to light incense the other day?

438
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:48,891
I want to make amends, even if just a little bit...

439
00:36:48,891 --> 00:36:53,231
Is burning incense while keeping quiet about the truth atonement?

440
00:36:56,495 --> 00:36:58,495
Because I thought I couldn't take it back...

441
00:36:58,495 --> 00:37:00,165
If I find out, I have no way to take it back.

442
00:37:00,165 --> 00:37:02,297
Because you thought so, right?

443
00:37:04,627 --> 00:37:07,825
The reason why I said "let's run away" in the first place

444
00:37:07,825 --> 00:37:12,825
It's you, right? Because I don't want my affair to be found out.

445
00:37:12,825 --> 00:37:17,033
Ah... and that

446
00:37:17,033 --> 00:37:20,594
I started telling her to go collect the receipts.

447
00:37:23,099 --> 00:37:29,726
What did he say at that time?

448
00:37:29,726 --> 00:37:33,792
The dream is...

449
00:37:33,792 --> 00:37:37,825
"I can't hide it any longer"...

450
00:37:37,825 --> 00:37:42,066
"Let's be honest about everything"...

451
00:37:44,198 --> 00:37:50,429
What did you say to stop it?

452
00:37:50,429 --> 00:37:53,198
Eh... alive...

453
00:37:53,198 --> 00:37:54,858
“Living”?

454
00:37:59,726 --> 00:38:06,462
When I told you the truth

455
00:38:06,462 --> 00:38:09,594
Because it won't come back to life

456
00:38:09,594 --> 00:38:14,957
♬〜

457
00:38:14,957 --> 00:38:21,891
I was scared... I met you when I moved.

458
00:38:21,891 --> 00:38:24,792
I heard you had a suicide note...

459
00:38:26,627 --> 00:38:28,891
Why did you do that?

460
00:38:28,891 --> 00:38:32,858
What about the will? Huh?

461
00:38:32,858 --> 00:38:38,066
Will What were you planning to do?

462
00:38:43,231 --> 00:38:48,693
I said, "Throw it away."

463
00:38:50,429 --> 00:38:52,759
Haha...

464
00:38:56,825 --> 00:38:59,594
Um... really...

465
00:38:59,594 --> 00:39:04,792
Even so, Yume always had the suicide note.

466
00:39:04,792 --> 00:39:06,462
Huh?

467
00:39:12,363 --> 00:39:21,330
(cry)

468
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:27,033
(cry)

469
00:39:28,231 --> 00:39:36,627
(breathing heavily)

470
00:39:36,627 --> 00:39:39,033
Ah!

471
00:39:39,033 --> 00:39:47,000
(breathing heavily)

472
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:26,000
(sound of waves)

473
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:46,000
(sound of waves)

474
00:40:46,000 --> 00:41:06,066
(sound of waves)

475
00:41:06,066 --> 00:41:23,495
(sound of waves)

476
00:41:23,495 --> 00:41:28,396
Hahahaha hehe

477
00:41:30,693 --> 00:41:32,363
Hehehehe

478
00:41:33,528 --> 00:41:38,033
Haha hehehehe

479
00:41:38,033 --> 00:41:40,297
Hahahaha

480
00:41:42,594 --> 00:41:44,891
Hahahahaha

481
00:41:54,363 --> 00:41:56,363
Haha... (noise)

482
00:42:00,495 --> 00:42:02,165
Mio-chan?

483
00:42:05,033 --> 00:42:07,264
Mio-chan!

484
00:42:07,264 --> 00:42:27,264
♬〜

485
00:42:27,264 --> 00:42:30,330
♬〜

486
00:42:30,330 --> 00:42:50,396
♬〜

487
00:42:50,396 --> 00:43:10,396
♬〜

488
00:43:10,396 --> 00:43:30,396
♬〜

489
00:43:30,396 --> 00:43:32,066
♬〜

490
00:43:32,066 --> 00:43:48,231
♬〜

491
00:43:48,231 --> 00:43:51,495
(chime)

492
00:43:51,495 --> 00:44:04,825
♬〜

493
00:44:15,231 --> 00:44:20,066
(Chihiro) Sorry for the inconvenience, this is Yume Nakata's mother.

494
00:44:26,033 --> 00:44:29,000
Now... can I have a moment?

495
00:44:39,495 --> 00:44:42,594
(Chihiro) No matter what I do, I can't make up for it with you anymore.

496
00:44:42,594 --> 00:44:44,429
One more chance to try again...

497
00:44:44,429 --> 00:44:46,396
That girl and I were friends

498
00:44:46,396 --> 00:44:48,132
I want to pretend it all never happened anymore

499
00:44:48,132 --> 00:44:49,858
Go!

500
00:44:49,858 --> 00:44:53,000
I was the one who couldn't forgive my mother the most.
